  "prompt": "I have a crush on a girl and do not have courage to propose to her. What should I do to tell her that I like her?",
  "response": "It's completely natural to feel nervous when it comes to expressing your feelings to someone you care about. Here are some steps you can take to help you muster the courage and approach the situation thoughtfully:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings:**\n   - Take some time to understand why you like her and what you hope for in the relationship. This clarity can give you confidence when you decide to share your feelings.\n\n2. **Build a Connection:**\n   - Strengthen your existing relationship by spending more time together. Engage in conversations, share interests, and create positive experiences that can make both of you feel more comfortable.\n\n3. **Choose the Right Moment:**\n   - Find a quiet, private setting where you both can talk without interruptions. Choosing the right time can make the conversation more meaningful and less stressful.\n\n4. **Be Honest and Direct:**\n   - When you're ready, speak from the heart. You might say something like, \"I've really enjoyed getting to know you, and I wanted to share that I have feelings for you.\"\n\n5. **Prepare for Any Response:**\n   - Understand that she might need time to process her feelings, or she might not feel the same way. Be prepared to respect her response, whatever it may be, and maintain your composure.\n\n6. **Stay Positive:**\n   - Regardless of the outcome, taking the step to express your feelings is brave and can lead to personal growth. If things don't turn out as you hoped, it doesn't diminish your worth or the potential for future relationships.\n\n7. **Seek Support:**\n   - Talk to trusted friends or family members about how you're feeling. They can offer encouragement and advice based on their own experiences.\n\n8. **Practice What You Want to Say:**\n   - Sometimes rehearsing can help reduce anxiety. Practice expressing your feelings out loud or write them down to organize your thoughts.\n\nRemember, vulnerability is a strength, and expressing your true feelings is an important step toward building meaningful connections. Whatever happens, you\u2019re taking a courageous step toward honesty and authenticity in your relationships.",
